                            <comment id="17819815" author="norrisjeremy" created="Thu, 22 Feb 2024 21:08:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, the sooner 1.26.1 can be released the better so that we don&apos;t have to manually add a dependency to commons-codec.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17820986" author="manusa" created="Tue, 27 Feb 2024 06:38:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the quick turnaround, this change was also breaking the Fabric8 Kubernetes Client (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/fabric8io/kubernetes-client/pull/5757&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/fabric8io/kubernetes-client/pull/5757&lt;/a&gt;) especially in downstream dependent projects where we had no clue what was going on.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17821116" author="norrisjeremy" created="Tue, 27 Feb 2024 09:30:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any news on when 1.26.1 will be released so that TarArchiveOutputStream is once again usable without projects have to add an explicit dependency on commons-codec?&lt;br/&gt;
This seems fairly important since 1.26.0 includes security fixes and is effectively broken for users of TarArchiveOutputStream.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
